Dr. Blagovo (1867-1940) had married at the age of forty a provincialbelle in the Volgan town of Kineshma, a few miles south from one of my mostromanic country estates, famous for its wild ravines, now gravel pits orplaces of massacre, but then magnificent evocations of sunken gardens. Shewore elaborate make-up and spoke in simpering accents, reducing nouns